    public class CloseableUncertainIterator<T>

    • Constructor Detail

      • CloseableUncertainIterator

        public CloseableUncertainIterator(java.util.Queue<T> queue)
        Construct this using the given queue for data. When the queue has data hasNext() will reeturn UncertainIterator.HAS_NEXT.TRUE. When the queue is empty hasNext() will return UncertainIterator.HAS_NEXT.MAYBE. When the queue is empty and this object has been close()ed, then UncertainIterator.HAS_NEXT.FALSE is returned.
        Parameters:
        queue - The queue to read elements from.
